Setting up a dev environment for class2go
=========================================

General Instructions
* Set-up Python
* Set-up Python's virtual env
* Set-up Django
* Set-up Mysql



For MAC OS-X Lion: Instructions mainly taken from 
http://www.tlswebsolutions.com/mac-os-x-lion-setting-up-django-pip-virtualenv-and-homebrew/

1. Install Homebrew:
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(/usr/bin/curl -fksSL https://raw.github.com/mxcl/homebrew/master/Library/Contributions/install_homebrew.rb)"

2. Install Python:
brew install readline sqlite gdbm 
brew install python --universal --framework 

3. Install mysql
brew install mysql
(Optional but useful for looking at the database)
Install phpmyadmin (?!) following the directions here:
http://www.djangoapp.com/blog/2011/07/24/installing-phpmyadmin-on-mac-os-x-lion/

4. Install pip, a python package manager
easy_install pip

5. Install python's virtual env
pip install virtualenv 

6. Use the class2go virtual env (django-class2go directory under the directory where this README is found)
(hopefully this will make steps 7-10 already complete when you check out the git repo.  You can run the 
commands for 7-10.  The repo will at least save you some downloads, hopefully).
source django-class2go/bin/activate 

7. Install django itself (this will be inside the virtualenv)
pip install django

8. Install MySQL-python (this will be inside the virtualenv)
pip install http://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/mysql-python/mysql-python-test/1.2.3c1/MySQL-python-1.2.3c1.tar.gz?use_mirror=cdnetworks-us-2 

9. Install python image library (this will be inside the virtualenv)
pip install PIL

10. Install South, the database schema migration tool: (this will be inside the virtualenv)
easy_install South

11. Setup initial db.
./manage.py syncdb
./manage.py migrate

